Abducted former chairman of Federated Correspondents’ Chapel of the Nigeria Union of Journalists, Bayelsa State Council, Julius Olusegun Osahon, has been freed from captivity.Osahon was kidnapped around 8:00pm on Sunday, March 28, 2022 by gunmen suspected to be Fulani herdsmen along Patani area of the East-West Road. He was released on Friday night.The kidnappers had earlier demanded a N5million ransom for his release but later increased it to about N50million.Osahon and about 17 other passengers were travelling in a commercial bus marked Sunny Eru Motors when they were kidnapped by gunmen along the Patani area of the East-West Road. The bus driver was shot dead by the attackers in the incident.